dashboardItems.text:
*Coverage of standards and benchmarks assessments*
This dashboard displays the status of carrying out standards and benchmarks assessments globally, including which countries have had a repeat assessment.
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

dashboards.name: 01. Coverage of standards and benchmarks assessments

dashboardItems.text:
*Assessment line list*
The table below shows the results for each standard for all standards and benchmarks assessments carried out.

*Changes (improvements vs worsening) for each standard*
These two charts show the number of countries that improved (left chart, green) or worsened (right chart, red) on each standard.
Net change compares the latest assessment with first assessment carried out in a country.

*Aggregate results by standard*

This chart shows the proportion of countries that met, partially met or did not meet each standard at their latest standards and benchmarks assessment.
Numbers in the bars represent the number of countries.
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE
SPACER_ITEM_FOR_DASHBOARD_LAYOUT_CONVENIENCE

*Summary scores and net change for surveillance standards* 

Met = 3 points
Partially met = 1 point
Not met = -1 point
Not assessed/not applicable = 0 points

The net change is calculated by comparing the latest standards and benchmarks assessment with the first assessment carried out in each country.
*Summary score and net change for all surveillance standards: B1.1-B2.3 (data quality, system coverage, vital registration, surveillance among special populations combined)*

*Summary scores and net change for system coverage standards: B1.8-B1.9*
*Summary scores and net change for data quality standards: B1.1-B1.7*

*Summary scores and net change for data quality and system coverage standards*

Met = 3 points
Partially met = 1 point
Not met = -1 point
Not assessed/not applicable = 0 points

The net change is calculated by comparing the latest standards and benchmarks assessment with the first assessment carried out in each country.

This dashboards counts the number of times a recommendation was made at the latest standards and benchmarks assessment. Higher numbers suggest priority areas that need to be addressed, in the form of developing resources (guidance, products, tools) or technical assistance.
